genresAdvancedInfo.name: nu electro
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Nu electro is a subgenre of electro music that emerged in the late 2000s. It is characterized by its use of heavy basslines, distorted synths, and glitchy effects. Nu electro often incorporates elements of other genres such as techno, house, and hip hop, resulting in a sound that is both futuristic and nostalgic. With its high-energy beats and edgy sound, nu electro is a genre that is perfect for the dance floor.
